               <floruit>3rdC<ref corresp="#d2e34805"/>
               </floruit>
               <note xml:id="d2e34780" n="7"> This is a long story. At the beginning רבי
                                זעירא (Ze‘ira [4]) and a certain ר' ירמיה are seated together. This
                                could be Jeremiah (2). In the end of the episode we read אמר רבי
                                זעירה ... ירמיה בני (Said Rabbi Ze‘ira: … Jeremiah my son …). This
                                could be interpreted as a condescending epithet, but it could imply
                                a real family relationship, in which case this is another
                                Jeremiah.</note>
               <note xml:id="d2e34805" n="8"> See above, n. 5.</note>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
